Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

In November I stole 's purse (-30 points). In May I bought porn for (-10 points). In September I signed my organ donor card (28 points). In July I caught a purse-snatcher who stole 's purse (30 points). In June I gave change to a homeless guy (19 points).

Overall, I've been nice (37 points). For Christmas I deserve a pony!

Sincerely,
uarockgoddess40

omg. super thanks to all of you who came to my surprise b-day party and kept it totally secret! i was in shock! not even kidding. you all are amazing! omg!

okay...great quotes from last night:

"the birds!"
"when he comes up, we go down!"
"only in my head." "wait...in your hand?!"
"i'm sure he's a lot more familiar with ball sacks"
"you aren't a chesse breadstick...we're just comparing you to one"
"that is a really hot chesse breadstick"

uh...if u can think of more...tell me...i can't really remember all.

off to go shopping, do chores, and take my sis to chronicles of narnia. ttyl.

no school tomorrow!!!!! HELL YEA ALL!! this is amazing. we needed a snow day and we got one. i love it. i absolutly love it. i got a facebook tonight....so look for me there. yea....that's pretty sweet. i had to go to the dentist today....i have a caivty...it kinda bites. one of my teeth hurts too from them poking at it. ow!!!  it really hurts. i should prolly go take some advil or something. 

god....is it just me or do you hate when you're like sitting there spilling your guts to someone and they don't even bother responding? it drives me insane!!!! one of my biggest pet peeves. and then when you point it out to them all they can do is say how sorry they are...and they don't do anything to adress what you were talking to them about in the first place. god!!!    

i'm going to go and take some advil and lie down on my bed. bah...life sucks sometimes.

i'm sick of never being noticed. no one talks to me....no one notices me at parties....no guys like me...no one remembers me...i'm the invisible person. and truth be told....i'm sick of it. i'm sick of being constantly over shadowed by my friends like kt and suzy and tessa. no one notices me anymore. 

Example 1:
Meg and Kt walk into cast party.
"hi kt!"
"hey it's kt kuvin!"
"wow kt's here"
"yo kt, u made it"
s-white: "hey chopped liver" (but only after i commented on how no one noticed me)

Example 2:
Meg talking to person who shall not be named for their sake.
Meg: "and then....omg....i was so upset. can you believe it?!"
Person x: "oh...wait...u were talking....what??"



no more examples needed. i'm the invisible person and it sucks. no one loves me....no one cares....and chances are everyone will forget my b-day again this year.

~Meg

Reminder to All: Meg's b-day=December 1st

i'm kinda hoping that by posting this....every will remember....unlike last year where no one knew a thing about it until the said it on the announcements. twas quite depressing.

also....meg is still in need of a date to winter dance. suggestions and set-ups welcome.

~Meg

well this enitre past week was both amazing and tiring and painful and perfect. i love everyone.

monday: let's see....i know that i had oliver which was amazing but really long. and i hung out w/ ppl after school if i remember correctly. and yea....that was cool. oh yea....was supossed to burn cds for pit for oliver and was going to go home and do it...drove all the way home to realize that the disk i was burning was at school so drove back and burnt it there after dinner in the cafe.

tuesday: let's see...i skipped jazz band to do pit-ish things.....hung out w/ ppl....had oliver....didn't do any hw....came home and slept.

wednesday: band banquet cancelled cause bob had no voice....chose instead to hang out and do pit stuff.....dinner....party on....oliver....home....skip hw....sleep.

thursday: uber short day of school. came home and got hair cut. skipped jazz band. OLIVER PREFORMANCE!!! amazingness. and yea....home to sleep.

friday: career shadowing at lakota. pretty sweet hanging out w/ all my old band directors and eating lunch in the teacher's lounge of my old school and seeing all my old teachers. not gonna lie....it was pretty sweet. then home for a short nap. met kt for dinner at steak and shake. than oliver again. pretty fun.

saturday: woke up. filled out job application for old navy. went to target with me mater and bought lots of pretty sweet stuff. dinner. OLIVER!!! drove home. dropped some stuff off. went to the cast party and john's house. stayed there till 12:30. came home where kt and i crashed.

sunday: woke up. went to church. ate lunch. ran off to OLIVER!!! with kt. saw mama!!! *squee* i love her!!! so much!!! ran off to CYWE rehearsal. had a super boring rehersal. toby pisses me off like none other. i hate that kid. and came home, had some bread for dinner. talked to ppl. still no hw done. off to bed now. 

 

i love you all. thanks for making this the most perfect amazing busy and stressful week of my life. thanks to all the new friends i've made (ryan) and all the friendships that have just gotten closer. i love you all.

 

~Meg

well today was pretty right off. let's see....late arrival *yes!!!!*......classes....a free....some classes....A+ in anatomy for the quarter....blah blah blah....stupid stuff....oh yea...4th chair district 14 honor band (one chair over jon hogan....hehehe)....A on evil paper ^_^ giving me an A- for the quarter.....rushing home.....forgetting OLIVER cd to burn....rushing back to school....eating and burning OLIVER cds.....PIT SET UP!!!!!!!....mad rushing to prepare for rehearsal...missing warm-up b/c stand lights suck....rehearsal....PIT TEAR DOWN....almost breaking the xylophone....and finally home. so yea....some stress....lots of good. i got a new phone....that....works now. pretty sweet. and yea....that's about all. i love u all. ttyl. sleep time and not doing any hw for me now. party on!

~Meg

hey all.

well...last night was so insanely add. well.....brandon came at like 6:45 to pick me up. we went to rave...no one was there yet. called ppl and everyone was "almost there". everyone showed and we decided not to see a movie, so we went to steak and shake. no one would serve us there so we decided to go to starbucks. we went to starbucks and hung out and drank coffee and talked and played games out of this weird as hell book. then we decided to go the park....so brandon and i leave and go there and when we get there, only lyss and matt are there. we call everyone else and apparently they all decided to go over to Ally's house. so we decided to hang out at the park for a bit. brandon and matt spun themselves on the tire swings until they almost hurled, lyss and i almost broke the swingset and we had massive fun on the seesaw until matt got hit in the stomach w/ the grip bars on one of them. lol. we listened to music for a bit and then went over to ally's. watched robots. brandon left like halfway through so matt drove me home. i think i fell asleep during the movie....but it's all good. got home late. crashed. woke up late. so yea...pretty sweet night. got some cleaning to do now. peace and love all. i'll talk to you later.


~Meg

well....today let's see. failed an anatomy test. forgot my book for latin. almost fell asleep during music theory (and succeeded in fighting through the whole class w/ kt) ignored lavely's boringness in english, tried to pay attention in a boring world civ class....oh yea....and then there was evil. yea....let's not go there. basically....conservative class, original sin, sex and yea....me, caitlin, heather and a bit of rachel lang. not very fun at all. quite upsetting at that. but yea.....the liberal corner of the room had some fun but stayed good. anatomy lab make up after school...waste of 20 minutes. i could've gotten all that shit out of the book anyways. lots of hw to do tonight. civ project due tomorrow that i haven't started yet. 

ally: if u see this...call me and we'll find some date to stay after school. 

caitlin kane: u are my life. we need to talk later. i'll im u tonight if u're on. sorry about today. we'll talk about that later

katie: sorry we fought today and i'll consider joining u.

alyssa malpede: call me bout friday.

sarah white: i need details for friday night.

brandon: wanna do something this weekend or next? im me later.

 

that's all for now. more later.

~Meg

well...i haven't updated in forever...so...here it goes.

my room is now red. yes...real red...not fake red...real red. and there is cork board on the walls which is pretty sweet at life

anti homecoming party...my house...saturday...which is going to be really really sweet at life. and...yea...grades are good. getting the dude whose car i hit is going to cost about $1200 but eh..not terrible i guess. well...that's all i got to say. ttyl. ^_^ <3

ps. carlton monroe is my life 
pps. Phil is my love and my life!!! *squee*

i don't know why it hurts...but it does. 

all of my friends are being asked to moeller homecoming and i'm not. i wouldn't want to go if i was asked...i think moeller dance...and well...dances in general...are retarded...and in fact i'm having an anti-dance party the day of homecoming (ps...everyone come...it's going to rock) but i still feel shitty. if you have any reason to make me feel better...feel free to leave it. god i need to meet some new guys.

cywe audtion sucked. scales went well, sight reading went well, rest of it sucked. yea...it bites.

but i'm in sinfonia now. so yea. nuff said. ttyl.

new s/n: selmer sax girl

ps. I <3 Allison Turner ^_^

mmkay..update on the past few days. band is life. cerfews suck. the mama cd(s)=my life in a box. drum corp is amazing still. and i'm dead tired so i'm going to bed. more later

well...this week has been totally awesome. 

yesterday: can't remember wut i did during the day...must not have been important. i did work out though and that was cool. oh...and i got my CYWE exerpts....and they're really hard. gah! i'm never going to be able to get in *rant* but yea...then i was looking for something to do and talked to david and was going to go see charlie and the chocolate factory w/ david and toph but we ended up being like half an hour late for the movie so we went put-putting which was awesome (toph lost...he's a terrible golfer) and then went to steak and shake for shakes and frys. got home late...there was a party going on at my house...but then i went to bed cause i was tired. ended up falling asleep at 2 in the morningish.

today: woke up at 8! (yes 8!) in the morning. practice piano for a bit....then went to my piano lesson @ 10. my piano teacher loves me now cause he thinks i actually practice a lot but really i've just gotten an assload better at sightreading. so....yea....that was fun. then i came home for like two minutes to grab the key the ppl that i'm house sitting for's house. went to their house and watered the plants and brought some boxes into their garage and spilled toxic chemmicals on my hand which kinda sucked. then i went home for like two more minutes and vaccumed and stuff and then i went to ritter's and put a hold on a cake and bought a shake and stuff. then i came home and ate lunch and did dishes and then went off the the mall to hang out w/ kt. met kt...did...stuff. ran into kitkat and went to visit erin. ate dinner at sabarro's which was really really good. then it was off to band practice! band was fun....lots of boring frosh stuff though but the new frosh are cool ppl even if they can't march and i <3 all of the other ppl and i got to see old ppl which rocked. then off to skyline w/ david and frosh fazz. tons of fun there. then came home and wrote this while on the phone w/ kt and that's about it. so yea...i'm off to bed.

mostly today i did stuff and talked to kt. kt and i fought....a lot....today. but we still stayed on the phone for over 2 hours. yay kt! boo on kt and parents....she didn't come to my party last night. boo kt. but i love kt anyways. ^_^ yay for loving kt.

party last night...was totally awesome. we watched matrix 2. and ate food. and planned the entire party w/ 2 hours of notice. well...i'm off. custard! yay! 

oh...and ps...i <3 kt.

hello my loverly xanga readers. i'm so sorry i have been neglecting you so. i haven't had much to say....except for the fact that i did leave all of you out on my adventures in drum corp world. if you really want to read all about that feel free to pop by my livejournal or inquire within. whichever...i'm open for anything.

okay...update on the past few days: 

saturday: only noteable things...i went to my sax lesson where my new teacher noticed (and you really are never going to believe this in like 1001 years) that i have a self confidence issue *GASP* hahaha. yea...that was amusing. then i worked. that was about it. oh. and i read harry potter and called kt...but those are givens.

sunday. i went to church. then took erin to wendy's/the bank/her work. then i ran home and grabbed the cell phone charger before running off to kt and smw's voice recital. some ppl sang really well....some ppl sang not so well. kt and smw's duet went really well. everyone cracked up at their costumes. then i stole kt and drove her to rave (smw couldn't come b/c she had to go to this cast party for her sis+this rehearsal thing) and we saw charlie and the chocolate factory, which fyi is a totally awesome and majorly drugged out beyond reason movie. i loved it. danny elfman is my life. and tim burton/johnny deppness is pretty damn cool too. sooo...ummm...yea. don't remember what i did after that. i really don't. oh...i remember now...i got uber depressed and then got reallly incredibly highly happy and called kt and then i watched this amazing movie called impromptu and then talked to kt on the phone until like 3 in the morning and then i went to bed. 

monday: woke up. drug myself around my daily tasks. asked me mater if i could go visit sarah white...mom bitched in response. sent a couple of very emotionally driven emails. went to work. talked w/ mouse for the first time in awhile. came home. talked to kt until 12:30ish. watched dumb tv. drug self into bed.

today: chores. got mom's b-day present. talked to kt and sarah. got and equally emotionally driven response to one of my emotionally driven emails from monday. cried a bit. scheduled next sat prep lesson >_< now: looking for plans to do tonight. 

well...i'm off to go and find ppl to do stuff with. i'll talk to you all later.

everyone please say a quick prayer for caroline sim. the mall she was in in Israel was bombed by a suicide bomber. she is fine but at the current time 3 members of the group she was with are missing. she has high hopes of them being found but there is no guarentee right now.

so...okay. yesterday=amazing!!!

basically...i woke-up at 10 am for no real reason and just u know...got dressed, threw my contacts in, grabbed a diet coke and drove over to bp to get gas in my car. as i drove past lakota west i noticed that capital regiment was already out so after filling my car up w/ gas i drove over. then i proceeded to wander around for...oh...10 minutes cause i had forgotten to bring mama's cell number w/ me...but...oh well...before i actually found her at the food truck. so...i got pulled onto the food truck and got the quick tour of it...(okay...quick food truck discription...it's an 18 wheeler on but on the inside there are stoves, 3 sinks for washing dishes, 2 freezers, 3 crockpots, 2 ovens, a shower?!, a washer and dryer, and like all the food you could ever possibly imagine) and then as soon as my tour was over she put me to work helping make lunch for the 150 people drum corp. basically my job was to put fruit in the freezer, give fruit to kenny after it was all cold, peeling eggs (which really sucked because someone forgot to dunk them in cold water after they were boiled), going to skyline w/ one of that parents w/ hopes of being able to afford skyline for a meal for everyone (ps...west chester skyline sucks ass!!!!), setting our plastic forks knives and spoons, handing mama towels, setting up the food outside of the food truck and then serving fruit cocktail to all the kids until i had to leave and give erin back the car. I got there at 10:30, i left at 1:30. 

so...ya know. i went home and practiced for a bit, did some psat prep course stuff cause parents suck, watched tv, finished the He's A Pirate arrangment (which ended up becomeing a medley of pirates themes) and playing sax until i realized i needed to go get a new belt. so i called my mom and met her at old navy at like 5:30 and did some quick shopping, got home around 6. called toph back, ate a quick dinner or like 5 soy hot wings and went to pick up toph to drive back to west for capital's rehearsal.

went back to west. this time knew that i'd find everyone i wanted to find at the food truck. saw a bunch of old lakota ppl i didn't want to see, and then (on mama's orders) drug toph over to the corp so that i could brainwash him. unfortunately, the corp wasn't on any of the main fields so toph and i got really really really lost before we did find them eventually. watched them on the soccer field and then we all (w/ the corp) wandered back to the main field for the run-through and real practice. went up and sat w/ mama who tried to get me and toph to go home, grab a sleeping bag and then come back and join the corp for the rest of the tour, him on tuba, me on baritone. parents didn't like that idea though even though i was all for it. *le sigh* but u know...got to talk to mama for awhile, watched the corp being amazing, laughed at mama for her so-called "idiosyncrosies", talked about mr. monroe, talked to a bunch of parents on how to convince my parents to let me do the corp next season, saw a bunch of ppl i knew from grade school who pretended they had no idea who i was (i waved ^_^) and basically just had a totally amazing time. after the run-through mama ran back to cook skyline dip for their late night snack and toph and i went back to my car which we had parked over by the other field and then drove back over to say bye to mama (which went really well fyi) and then it was back home for some actual dinner at...oh...11:30 at night. 

so...to sum up yesterday in a box...i spent 12 hours w/ drum corp almost, i MUST join the corp, capital=amazing, and oh yea...mama=perfect.

welp...now i'm off to go buy some new reeds and then practice and shit today for the 6 hours until i leave to go to the drum corp contest in centerville. i will right about that all tomorrow. ^_^ oh yea...and the bf who lives in indiana, he's in dayton for the week...seeing him tomorrow. wel...ttyl.

well...working again tonight. should be fun. i'm working w/ some amazing ppl that i love dearly. 

got amazing tickets to drum corp contest. *is uber excited* i have no idea when the rehearsal is on monday that i promised mama i'd come to...oh well...i guess i'll just open the windows in my house and when the amazingness music that is drum corp comes floating through my house i will then know that it is time to go and visit her. ^_^ gah...i'm totally drum corp obsessed!! i should totally be in a corp myself but my stupid parentals said that i "don't have time" and....truth be told....they're probably right...but i just....i wish i could do it. i love marching w/ a passion....i wish that i could do it all summer as well as football season...but alas...i cannot. stupid moeller only having 2 real summer rehearsals. oh well...i'm going to a drum corp contest! *w00t*

well...off to go do stuff and then to work 7-cl. be on whenever they let me leave. ttyl. <3

PS: New song under production for next years Ursuline Band....He's A Pirate! party on. du du dut dut du du dut dut ^_^

well everyone. the deadline for ordering tickets to the dci contest has ended...well...ordering tickets through me that is. i mailed in the order form today with only a ticket for me, suzy, and whoever is driving me all the way to centerville. if you still wanna go...i'll give u the website for ticket orders.

if you are coming w/ me to the centerville drum corp contest...tell me now and how many seats u will need so that i can order tickets...i'll call everyone that expressed intrest earlier but if you didn't know about it then and want to go now...send me an im or call me.

well...guess who is feeling sick as a dog...


if you guessed me...you're probably right. i feel like total crap. headache, dizzy, sore throat, stomach ache. no fever..but i still feel really crappy. well...mayb after a long sleep tonight i'll feel better. one can only hope...right?

on a good note though...phillip's mom got a hold of a mark VI alto that she is considering selling and if she does decide to sell i get first look at it ^_^ yay for having a guy whose mom is a sax obsessive too ^_^ i'm excited. if i can get her to go below 2,000 i have to go for it...yea...i don't really have that type of money...but they usually run about 4,500-6,000 and if i can get her to sell it to me cheep i'm going for it. ^_^

well...off to finish packing. driving home tomorrow....12 hour drive home. *sigh* at least i have plenty of movies to keep me company and more than enough cds to make me happy. 

missing eveyone much

~Meg

i need a new layout. if anyone is intrested...i will give you my username and password to my account so u can come and do it if that is what you need. i don't know shit about layouts so someone good...please come and help me!!!

~Meg

welllll.....things about today. randomly talked to my ex-bf, david, yesterday. haven't spoken to him in awhile. i think he wants to get back togethter though...and i'm not sure. oh well...we're hitting up a movie later this weekk....so...we'll see...we'll see. 

today: looks like it might be another stromy north carolina day. :( it's quite saddening..but i can hardly walk anyways because of two giant blisters on the soles of my big toes. it's quite depressing. today will prolly be a day of laying out in the hammock reading salinger. ^_^ man do i love salinger. ^_^ very muchly. also...i've been having the worst pain in my neck and i can't crack it...it's really pissing me off. going to try to get a massage from my sis later to see if that helps. i hope it does. 

tomorrow: leaving at 7 in the morning for the 12 hour drive back to cincy. if you wanna do something either that evening or the next day, call me on my dad's cell if you know it....or just call my house and i'll check messages on the drvie home and get back to you. well...i'm off to actually go wake-up, get my salinger, and head down to the beach before the rain comes. ttfn.

~Meg
